[u]Effortless Backup and Restore[/u]
No more manually recreating junction boxes and risking data loss. Junction Box Utils simplifies the process with its intuitive backup and restore feature. Select the junction box to delete, hit "Backup properties", proceed with deletion, then effortlessly restore all settings ‚Äî including name, address, turn restrictions, guidance, and lanes ‚Äî when recreating the junction box. Plus, Backup/Restore isn't limited to roundabouts ‚Äî it's a versatile tool for any junction box.
[b]Usage:[/b]¬†Select a junction box to backup its properties via a designated button in the edit panel. Recreate the junction box and use the appropriate button to restore its properties.
[b]Limitations[/b]
[list=1]
[*]Only available if the topology (the segments constructing the junction box) hasn‚Äôt been changed. This means you can do whatever you want, except¬†including/excluding segments. Changing the ID (merging/splitting) of those segments will affect the topology as well.
